LATAM – Starter kit

OpenVent_mCherry (pTI):
Works both for Cellular Reagents and as purified enzyme. 
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator.
Resistance: Kanamycin.

Taq* (pET28):
Used in Cerda et al 2021, it comes from Graham et al. 2021. Also available in Addgene (Addgene plasmid # 166944; http://n2t.net/addgene:166944 and https://gitlab.com/tjian-darzacq-lab/bearmix  
Protocol: https://www.protocols.io/view/recombinant-protein-expression-and-purification-of-q26g78ew8lwz/v1 
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator.
Resistance: Kanamycin.

oMMLV (Superscript) (pET19-b):
Tried  in  C41, pLysS y BL21, but i didn´t produce much protein. Successfully used pET19_MMLV from Matute et al., 2021 
Protocol: https://www.protocols.io/view/recombinant-expression-and-purification-of-codon-o-8epv515wdl1b/v2 
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator.
Resistance: Ampicillin. 

Bst-LF (pTI):
Successfully used in several DE3 expression strains, including BL21(DE3) and pLysS:
Protocol: https://www.protocols.io/view/recombinant-protein-expression-and-purification-of-ewov14j8yvr2/v1
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator.
Resistance: Kanamycin. 

HIV-RT (pTI):
Tested it successfully in E. coli strains C41(DE3) and BL21(DE3) (unpub. But we got a lot of data) 
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator.
Resistance: Kanamycin.

Pfu Sso7d (pET28):
Used in Cerda et al 2021, and got it from Dr. Alexander Klenov at York University.
Protocol: https://www.protocols.io/view/recombinant-protein-expression-and-purification-of-j8nlke17dl5r/v2 
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator.
Resistance: Kanamycin.

fuGFP_HisTag (pTI):
Assembled for purification: His-tag upstream the N-terminal region of fuGFP.
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator. 
Resistance: Kanamycin.

mScarlet-I (pTI): 
Assembled for constitutive expression using the native machinery of E.coli. 
Constitutive J23101 promotor. No his-tag.
Resistance: Kanamycin.

MScarlet-I_HisTag (pTI):
Assembled for purification: His-tag upstream the N-terminal region of fuGFP.
Expression is regulated by promotor T7 and Lac operator. 
Resistance: Kanamycin.


sfGFP (pTI):
Assembled for constitutive expression using the native machinery of E.coli. 
Constitutive J23101 promotor. No his-tag.
Resistance: Kanamycin.
